    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is definitely important - I think anyone who's had a notebook more than a couple of screens long wants some better way of organising and navigating it. There are various different ideas for solutions, though: tables of contents, collapsible sections, tabbed notebooks, and probably others that I don't remember.\n\nWe need to think about how much we want to pick one (or more) and build it into the notebook interface, or to offer APIs that third parties can use to build these kinds of features. I think my vote would be to build some fairly simple navigation system ourselves, because this is such a common need, but leave more advanced solutions to others. I envisage something like a button that you click to get a drop-down table of contents (and obviously clicking on the headers there jumps to that point in the document).\n"
  },
