    "updated_at": "2013-08-07T15:03:41Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I guess this would only apply to the IPython Notebook interface, so while editing the notebook?\n\nAsking because I see two main approaches:\n1. Implementing some fancy automatic table of contents with links in the notebook editor, possibly with the option of showing it from the menu and hiding it.\n2. Having some way of specifying in the notebook itself that you want a table of contents, probably at some specific location.\n\nI think there are use cases for both, but considering that there are more ways to use a notebook besides the notebook editor (as exported PDF, on the Notebook Viewer, etc) and a TOC could be implemented differently for each, I'd say that approach 2 would be most valuable.\n\nNot sure how to do this technically, but I could imagine some special construct in Markdown that is recognized by the editor and nbconvert, or perhaps a special TOC cell type.\n"
  },
